<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_arvīston" xml:lang="os-x-iron"><form type="lemma"><orth>arvīston</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>смесь сена с соломой в измельченном виде</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>chopped hay and straw mixture</q></cit></sense><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>смесь</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>mixture</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>сумятица</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>confusion</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>неразбериха</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>muddle</q></cit></sense><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/></sense><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>næ cardæj nyn arvīston yskodtoj; raxīz æmæ galīw kæm īs, ūj nal zonæm</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>они внесли сумятицу в нашу жизнь; мы уже не знаем, где право, где лево</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>they have brought confusion to our lives; we no longer know where is right, where is left</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>38</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>næ cardæj nyn arvīston yskodtoj; raxīz æmæ galīw kæm īs, ūj nal zonæm</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>они внесли сумятицу в нашу жизнь; мы уже не знаем, где право, где лево</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>they have brought confusion to our lives; we no longer know where is right, where is left</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Брит."/><biblScope>38</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">По облику -— отглагольное образование: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_a-"/> — преверб, %i-on%i — суффикс, %irvīst%i — прош. причастие от какого-то глагола со значением ‘сечь’, ‘крошить’ (ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>сечка</w></mentioned>). Предполагая закономерную перестановку %irvist%i ← %i*vrīst%i, приходим к <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>*braiš-: *brīšta</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>ломать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><w/><gloss><q>крошить</q></gloss></mentioned>,  и пр.; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/><w>vrī-: vrišk-</w><gloss><q>ломать</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">II 258 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">II 258 ff.</biblScope></bibl>). <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*braiš-</w></mentioned> представляет удлинение и.е. корня <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/><w>*bhrei-</w><gloss><q>резать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ine"><w/><gloss><q>крошить</q></gloss></mentioned>,  и пр., который распознается в <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>friare</w><gloss><q>растирать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>разбивать</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w>fricare</w><gloss><q>растирать</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="fr"><lang/><w>briser</w><gloss><q>разбивать</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fr"><w/><gloss><q>дробить</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note></mentioned>,  и пр. (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Pokorny"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">166 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">166 ff.</biblScope></bibl>). С удлинением %i-n%i мы находим этот же корень в ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lvynyn"/> ‘стричь’.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Formally, a deverbal derivation: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_a-"/> is a preverb, %i-on%i is a suffix, and %irvīst%i is a past participle of some verb with the meaning ‘shred’, ‘chop’ (cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>сечка</w><gloss><q>chaff</q></gloss></mentioned>). Assuming the natural alternation %irvist%i ← %i*vrīst%i, we reconstruct <mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><lang/><w>*braiš-: *brīšta</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>break</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="x-oldirn"><w/><gloss><q>chop</q></gloss></mentioned>,  etc.; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/><w>vrī-: vrišk-</w><gloss><q>break</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">II 258 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">II 258 ff.</biblScope></bibl>). <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>*braiš-</w></mentioned> is elongation of the Indo-European root <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/><w>*bhrei-</w><gloss><q>cut</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ine"><w/><gloss><q>chop</q></gloss></mentioned>,  etc., which is recognized in <mentioned xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>friare</w><gloss><q>grind</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="la"><w/><gloss><q>break</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="la"><w>fricare</w><gloss><q>grind</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="fr"><lang/><w>briser</w><gloss><q>break up</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="fr"><w/><gloss><q>fraction</q></gloss><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note><note type="comment" xml:lang=""> ()</note></mentioned>,  etc. (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Pokorny"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">166 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">166 ff.</biblScope></bibl>). With the elongation %i-n%i, we find the same root in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lvynyn"/> ‘cut’.</etym></entry>